[Modified from the android-rpi original to use the automotive specific config]

# Download Android source with local_manifests
 Refer to http://source.android.com/source/downloading.html

 $ repo init -u https://android.googlesource.com/platform/manifest -b android11-qpr3-release
 $ git clone https://github.com/klebert-engineering/ndslive_aaos_rpi-local_manifests .repo/local_manifests -b ke-main
 $ repo sync

# Build for Raspberry Pi 4
 https://github.com/klebert-engineering/ndslive_aaos_rpi/tree/ke-main

Use -j[n] option on sync & build steps, if build host has a good number of CPU cores.
